skills/goodwork/reference/state.md:3:This is the single source of truth for Goodwork v2 state. If a matcher, scheduler, approval flow, or presentation layer consumes it, it is JSON/JSONL. If a person or the interview consumes it, it is Markdown.
skills/goodwork/reference/state.md:7:One project folder is one person. The `goodwork/` folder holds state, vendored UI assets, the persistent Chrome profile, and a gitignored `.env`. Never install Goodwork globally. Degrade to draft-and-instruct when a capability is absent.
skills/goodwork/reference/state.md:11:The agent is the sole writer of state files. The server never mutates JSON or Markdown and never appends approvals; it only appends user request events to `events.jsonl`. The agent drains events, validates them, and writes resulting state changes.
skills/goodwork/reference/state.md:19:- `pipeline.json`: live CRM cards, inbound replies, and next actions.
skills/goodwork/reference/state.md:20:  Schema: `{version, updated_at, cards:[{id,target_id?,lead_id?,role,stage,warmth,last_touch_at?,next_action?,due_at?,owner,status,reason_code?,thread_ids:[],replies:[{id,channel,received_at,from,summary,stage_signal?,event_id?}],artifact_ids:[],approval_ids:[],proof_ids:[]}], unmatched_replies:[{id,channel,received_at,from,summary,match_candidates:[],status}]}`.
skills/goodwork/reference/state.md:21:- `leads.json`: posting leads found by `scout`, including the bench.
skills/goodwork/reference/state.md:23:- `sources.json`: boards, newsletters, communities, saved searches, and job channels.
skills/goodwork/reference/state.md:25:- `targets.json`: employer/segment target list and Top 10.
skills/goodwork/reference/state.md:27:- `capabilities.json`: setup results and best available execution rungs.
skills/goodwork/reference/state.md:29:- `metrics.json`: quotas, weekly funnel metrics, and the mutable evidence inbox index.
skills/goodwork/reference/state.md:30:  Schema: `{version, updated_at, quotas:{weekly_applications}, weeks:[{week_start,outreach_sent,applications,screens,interviews,offers,response_rate?,notes?}], evidence_inbox:[{id,event_id,source,profile_sections:[],claim,status,created_at,drained_at?}]}`.
skills/goodwork/reference/state.md:31:- `approvals.jsonl`: append-only agent-written approval records, one JSON object per line.
skills/goodwork/reference/state.md:33:- `events.jsonl`: append-only server-written request events, one JSON object per line.
skills/goodwork/reference/state.md:44:Legacy `TARGETS.md` and `PIPELINE.md` may be read during migration, but v2 authority is `targets.json` and `pipeline.json`.
skills/goodwork/reference/state.md:48:Profile-relevant events are tagged into `metrics.json.evidence_inbox`: lead approvals/dismissals, CV rejection reasons, recurring reply reason codes, stage-change patterns, and prototype debriefs. `profile` and `review` drain this inbox into dated `PROFILE.md` updates using the confidence-mark discipline, then mark inbox entries drained.
skills/goodwork/reference/assets.md:27:Updated documents (via eloquent where available), a proof-of-work plan appended to `goodwork/NICHE.md` with the artifact queue, and the consistency audit result. Nothing publishes without the user's explicit approval of the final text.
