goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-review.log:1550:1. **MCP connector.** Use connected services first. Email is Gmail drafts only; the user sends from Gmail, giving a physical send gate. Calendar connectors may propose slots and create drafts/holds only after approval.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-review.log:1553:4. **Manual fallback.** Produce the final draft, field-by-field instructions, and any files. The user performs the action.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-review.log:1555:When no rung is connected, degrade to draft-and-instruct. Do not silently skip an execution attempt; record the chosen rung or the fallback.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-review.log:1559:- **Approval gate.** Before any outbound draft creation, send, submit, publish, or browser final action, `approvals.jsonl` must contain a matching approval record.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-review.log:1560:- **Hash gate.** The approval `content_hash` must match the current artifact. A UI click is only a request; if content changed after render, re-present the artifact and do not approve.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-review.log:1562:- **Quota gate.** Weekly application quota in `metrics.json` is a hard cap. Do not exceed it without an explicit quota change recorded before execution.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-review.log:1568:Per-item approvals cover exactly one artifact. Session-batch approvals are allowed only when `covers` lists every item ID and content hash included in the batch.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-review.log:1570:Record schema lives in [state.md](state.md). Required fields: `id`, `timestamp`, `item_id`, `channel`, `granularity`, `content_hash`, `covers`, and `approved_by`. Include `source_event_id` when approval came from the UI.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-review.log:1574:An execution run is complete only when every requested outbound item has one of these states recorded against its pipeline card: executed with proof, draft created for user send, blocked by a named gate, or manual fallback produced.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-review.log:1581:Thirty minutes, once a week, same day each week. The review closes the loop between the campaign (what happened) and the profile (what it means). It reads `pipeline.json`, `targets.json`, `leads.json`, `metrics.json`, `JOURNAL.md`, `EXPERIMENTS.md`, `NICHE.md`, and `PROFILE.md`.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-review.log:1585:Pull the week's metrics from the pipeline: outreach sent, response rate, conversations, referrals, applications, screens, interviews, offers, source-of-interview. Compare to quota and to last week. Then run the funnel diagnosis from [pipeline.md](pipeline.md) — find the narrowest constriction and name which command fixes it. One diagnosis per week; don't change three variables at once or the next week's numbers mean nothing.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-review.log:1598:- Evidence inbox: drain `metrics.json.evidence_inbox` into `PROFILE.md` using [profile.md](profile.md). Do not leave profile-relevant campaign evidence stranded in JSON.
