goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-review.log:1655:Referrals and weak ties carry most opportunity; portals carry volume. This command runs the human layer: the listening tour, informational interviews, referral asks, cold outreach, and follow-up cadence. Execution uses [execution.md](execution.md); do not create drafts, send, or automate browser work without its approval and hash gates.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-review.log:1659:Read `capabilities.json` and [execution.md](execution.md) before turning any message into a Gmail draft, LinkedIn message, or manual send package. Gmail is draft-only; the user sends. Log the chosen rung and resulting thread IDs back to `pipeline.json`.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-review.log:1681:- After a conversation: thank-you within 24–72 hours, send anything promised, report back outcomes later ("took your advice, here's what happened" — the most underused relationship builder).
