goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:1472:+# execution - ladder, gates, approvals
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:1474:+This is the single source of truth for executing outbound Goodwork actions. Read it before any command creates a Gmail draft, sends, submits, publishes, uses ATS endpoints, or automates authenticated browser work.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:1478:+Consult `capabilities.json`; use the best available rung for the specific item.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:1480:+1. **MCP connector.** Use connected services first. Email is Gmail drafts only; the user sends from Gmail, giving a physical send gate. Calendar connectors may propose slots and create drafts/holds only after approval.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:1483:+4. **Manual fallback.** Produce the final draft, field-by-field instructions, and any files. The user performs the action.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:1485:+When no rung is connected, degrade to draft-and-instruct. Do not silently skip an execution attempt; record the chosen rung or the fallback.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:1489:+- **Approval gate.** Before any outbound draft creation, send, submit, publish, or browser final action, `approvals.jsonl` must contain a matching approval record.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:1490:+- **Hash gate.** The approval `content_hash` must match the current artifact. A UI click is only a request; if content changed after render, re-present the artifact and do not approve.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:1492:+- **Quota gate.** Weekly application quota in `metrics.json` is a hard cap. Do not exceed it without an explicit quota change recorded before execution.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:1498:+Per-item approvals cover exactly one artifact. Session-batch approvals are allowed only when `covers` lists every item ID and content hash included in the batch.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:1500:+Record schema lives in [state.md](state.md). Required fields: `id`, `timestamp`, `item_id`, `channel`, `granularity`, `content_hash`, `covers`, and `approved_by`. Include `source_event_id` when approval came from the UI.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:1504:+An execution run is complete only when every requested outbound item has one of these states recorded against its pipeline card: executed with proof, draft created for user send, blocked by a named gate, or manual fallback produced.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:1517:+Read [state.md](state.md), [execution.md](execution.md), `capabilities.json`, `pipeline.json`, `approvals.jsonl`, and `events.jsonl`. Use only capabilities recorded as available.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:1521:+1. Gmail via connector: replies, recruiter mail, interview logistics, rejection notices, and sent/draft status where available.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:1525:+Do not send from any channel during the sweep.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:1529:+Match inbound items to pipeline cards by thread IDs, sender/domain, company, role, URLs, and quoted content. If confidence is low, create an unmatched reply record and ask before changing a stage.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:1533:+Interview requests trigger calendar-slot proposals through the calendar connector when available. Draft replies only after applying the gates in [execution.md](execution.md).
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:1541:+Updated `pipeline.json`, drafted replies or calendar proposals awaiting approval, unmatched inbound items needing user judgment, and today's changed priorities for `daily`.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:1554:+Read `PROFILE.md`, `targets.json`, `sources.json`, `leads.json`, and the Top 10 targets before sweeping. If the profile is missing, run the short-form interview first.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:1558:+Build or update `sources.json` with boards, newsletters, community job channels, saved searches, recruiter lists, and niche-specific feeds. For each source record type, URL/query, niche tags, auth requirement, cadence, last sweep, and whether it is still alive.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:1564:+For each due source, collect current postings and verify they are live. Create or update `leads.json` records with stable IDs; do not duplicate a lead already seen through another source.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:1577:+Lead approvals, dismissals, and reason codes are profile evidence. Tag repeated patterns into the evidence inbox in `metrics.json` so `profile` or `review` can confront drift.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:1581:+Updated `sources.json` and `leads.json`, a ranked lead bench with reason codes, and any Top 10 target or profile drift flagged for `targets` or `profile`.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:1594:+1. Create or locate the one-person `goodwork/` workspace. Ensure `.env` is gitignored, initialize missing v2 state files from [state.md](state.md), and record any legacy Markdown files that need migration.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:1598:+5. Vendor `@pierre/diffs` into the workspace for the CV/application review page. Record vendor status in `capabilities.json`.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:1599:+6. Install or verify Tailscale as the default remote layer. Use `tailscale serve`, never `tailscale funnel`. If the user declines, record `desk-only`.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:1600:+7. Ask for reconcile cadence: `manual`, `on-demand`, or `scheduled`. Write it to `capabilities.json`.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:1601:+8. Run the live phone loop: start the local server, expose it through the tailnet when available, open the phone URL, tap the test button, confirm a test event lands in `events.jsonl`, and confirm the agent can drain it.
