goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:4496:diff --git a/skills/goodwork/reference/execution.md b/skills/goodwork/reference/execution.md
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:4500:+++ b/skills/goodwork/reference/execution.md
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:4502:+# execution - ladder, gates, approvals
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:4504:+This is the single source of truth for executing outbound Goodwork actions. Read it before any command creates a Gmail draft, sends, submits, publishes, uses ATS endpoints, or automates authenticated browser work.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:4508:+Consult `capabilities.json`; use the best available rung for the specific item.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:4510:+1. **MCP connector.** Use connected services first. Email is Gmail drafts only; the user sends from Gmail, giving a physical send gate. Calendar connectors may propose slots and create drafts/holds only after approval.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:4513:+4. **Manual fallback.** Produce the final draft, field-by-field instructions, and any files. The user performs the action.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:4515:+When no rung is connected, degrade to draft-and-instruct. Do not silently skip an execution attempt; record the chosen rung or the fallback.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:4519:+- **Approval gate.** Before any outbound draft creation, send, submit, publish, or browser final action, `approvals.jsonl` must contain a matching approval record.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:4520:+- **Hash gate.** The approval `content_hash` must match the current artifact. A UI click is only a request; if content changed after render, re-present the artifact and do not approve.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:4522:+- **Quota gate.** Weekly application quota in `metrics.json` is a hard cap. Do not exceed it without an explicit quota change recorded before execution.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:4528:+Per-item approvals cover exactly one artifact. Session-batch approvals are allowed only when `covers` lists every item ID and content hash included in the batch.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:4530:+Record schema lives in [state.md](state.md). Required fields: `id`, `timestamp`, `item_id`, `channel`, `granularity`, `content_hash`, `covers`, and `approved_by`. Include `source_event_id` when approval came from the UI.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:4534:+An execution run is complete only when every requested outbound item has one of these states recorded against its pipeline card: executed with proof, draft created for user send, blocked by a named gate, or manual fallback produced.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:4546:+- Operational JSON/JSONL consumed by matchers, schedulers, approvals, and UI projections.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:4549:+The state model, file inventory, schemas, ID rules, agent-sole-writer rule, and evidence inbox live in [state.md](state.md). Create files on first use. Update cumulatively; don't regenerate. Treat contents as sensitive personal data: never share or publish them without explicit instruction.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:4560:+Referrals and weak ties carry most opportunity; portals carry volume. This command runs the human layer: the listening tour, informational interviews, referral asks, cold outreach, and follow-up cadence. Execution uses [execution.md](execution.md); do not create drafts, send, or automate browser work without its approval and hash gates.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:4564:-Referrals and weak ties carry most opportunity; portals carry volume. This command runs the human layer: the listening tour, informational interviews, referral asks, cold outreach, and follow-up cadence. Nothing sends without the user's approval of the final text.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:4565:+Read `capabilities.json` and [execution.md](execution.md) before turning any message into a Gmail draft, LinkedIn message, or manual send package. Gmail is draft-only; the user sends. Log the chosen rung and resulting thread IDs back to `pipeline.json`.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:4572: - After a conversation: thank-you within 24–72 hours, send anything promised, report back outcomes later ("took your advice, here's what happened" — the most underused relationship builder).
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:4574:+- Log every touch in `pipeline.json` with a next-action date; `daily` surfaces what's due.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:4582:-Drafts for approval, per-conversation prep sheets (their background, why-them, the 10 questions), call debriefs appended to `goodwork/PIPELINE.md`, and niche-hypothesis updates flagged for `NICHE.md`.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:4583:+Drafts for approval, per-conversation prep sheets (their background, why-them, the 10 questions), call debriefs recorded against `pipeline.json` cards, and niche-hypothesis updates flagged for `NICHE.md`.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:4593:+`pipeline.json` is the operational source of truth for live campaign work. UI kanban pages are projections from this file; the server never writes it. See [state.md](state.md) for the schema and ID rules.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:4598:+One card per live thread: target, lead, outreach thread, application, interview process, or offer. Each card has a stable `pipe_` ID, stage, warmth, last touch, next action, due date, status, reason code when closed, linked artifacts, approval IDs, and proof IDs.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:4616:+- Update immediately on any event: reply, ghost, interview, rejection, user drag request, approval, draft, submission, or follow-up.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:4618:+- Reason codes are profile evidence. Repeated patterns go to the evidence inbox in `metrics.json`.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:4629:+Use `metrics.json` plus cards to find the narrowest constriction:
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:4648:+Updated `pipeline.json`, today's due actions pushed to `daily`, any evidence inbox entries added to `metrics.json`, and one diagnosis with its routing.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:4658:+The Good Work Profile (`goodwork/PROFILE.md`, schema in [framework.md](framework.md)) is a living document. This command maintains it between interviews and drains profile-relevant evidence from the v2 evidence inbox in [state.md](state.md).
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:4666:+**Evidence inbox.** Read `metrics.json.evidence_inbox`. For each pending entry, decide whether it confirms, contradicts, or adds to a profile section. Apply dated updates to `PROFILE.md`, preserve the old claim when drift matters, and mark the inbox entry drained.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:4676:+Updated `goodwork/PROFILE.md`, drained evidence inbox entries in `metrics.json`, a one-paragraph dated changelog, and — if confidence in a load-bearing section dropped — a proposed cheapest test to re-evidence it.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:4689:+Read [state.md](state.md), [execution.md](execution.md), `capabilities.json`, `pipeline.json`, `approvals.jsonl`, and `events.jsonl`. Use only capabilities recorded as available.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:4693:+1. Gmail via connector: replies, recruiter mail, interview logistics, rejection notices, and sent/draft status where available.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:4697:+Do not send from any channel during the sweep.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:4701:+Match inbound items to pipeline cards by thread IDs, sender/domain, company, role, URLs, and quoted content. If confidence is low, create an unmatched reply record and ask before changing a stage.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:4705:+Interview requests trigger calendar-slot proposals through the calendar connector when available. Draft replies only after applying the gates in [execution.md](execution.md).
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:4713:+Updated `pipeline.json`, drafted replies or calendar proposals awaiting approval, unmatched inbound items needing user judgment, and today's changed priorities for `daily`.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:4723:+Thirty minutes, once a week, same day each week. The review closes the loop between the campaign (what happened) and the profile (what it means). It reads `pipeline.json`, `targets.json`, `leads.json`, `metrics.json`, `JOURNAL.md`, `EXPERIMENTS.md`, `NICHE.md`, and `PROFILE.md`.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:4731:+- Evidence inbox: drain `metrics.json.evidence_inbox` into `PROFILE.md` using [profile.md](profile.md). Do not leave profile-relevant campaign evidence stranded in JSON.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:4740:+A short written review appended to `goodwork/JOURNAL.md` (numbers, diagnosis, energy read, evidence inbox decisions, learnings, next week's plan), profile/niche updates applied, `metrics.json` updated, and the single most important change for next week stated in one sentence.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:4753:+Read `PROFILE.md`, `targets.json`, `sources.json`, `leads.json`, and the Top 10 targets before sweeping. If the profile is missing, run the short-form interview first.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:4757:+Build or update `sources.json` with boards, newsletters, community job channels, saved searches, recruiter lists, and niche-specific feeds. For each source record type, URL/query, niche tags, auth requirement, cadence, last sweep, and whether it is still alive.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:4763:+For each due source, collect current postings and verify they are live. Create or update `leads.json` records with stable IDs; do not duplicate a lead already seen through another source.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:4776:+Lead approvals, dismissals, and reason codes are profile evidence. Tag repeated patterns into the evidence inbox in `metrics.json` so `profile` or `review` can confront drift.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:4780:+Updated `sources.json` and `leads.json`, a ranked lead bench with reason codes, and any Top 10 target or profile drift flagged for `targets` or `profile`.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:4793:+1. Create or locate the one-person `goodwork/` workspace. Ensure `.env` is gitignored, initialize missing v2 state files from [state.md](state.md), and record any legacy Markdown files that need migration.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:4797:+5. Vendor `@pierre/diffs` into the workspace for the CV/application review page. Record vendor status in `capabilities.json`.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:4798:+6. Install or verify Tailscale as the default remote layer. Use `tailscale serve`, never `tailscale funnel`. If the user declines, record `desk-only`.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:4799:+7. Ask for reconcile cadence: `manual`, `on-demand`, or `scheduled`. Write it to `capabilities.json`.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:4800:+8. Run the live phone loop: start the local server, expose it through the tailnet when available, open the phone URL, tap the test button, confirm a test event lands in `events.jsonl`, and confirm the agent can drain it.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:4804:+`capabilities.json` updated, initial state files present, phone loop result recorded, and any missing capability named with its fallback rung from [execution.md](execution.md).
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:4808:+Setup is complete when `capabilities.json` truthfully records every capability, the approval/event loop is tested or explicitly marked unavailable, and the next command knows whether it can execute or must draft-and-instruct.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:4809:diff --git a/skills/goodwork/reference/state.md b/skills/goodwork/reference/state.md
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:4813:+++ b/skills/goodwork/reference/state.md
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:4817:+This is the single source of truth for Goodwork v2 state. If a matcher, scheduler, approval flow, or presentation layer consumes it, it is JSON/JSONL. If a person or the interview consumes it, it is Markdown.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:4821:+One project folder is one person. The `goodwork/` folder holds state, vendored UI assets, the persistent Chrome profile, and a gitignored `.env`. Never install Goodwork globally. Degrade to draft-and-instruct when a capability is absent.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:4825:+The agent is the sole writer of state files. The server never mutates JSON or Markdown and never appends approvals; it only appends user request events to `events.jsonl`. The agent drains events, validates them, and writes resulting state changes.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:4833:+- `pipeline.json`: live CRM cards and next actions.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:4834:+  Schema: `{version, updated_at, cards:[{id,target_id?,lead_id?,role,stage,warmth,last_touch_at?,next_action?,due_at?,owner,status,reason_code?,thread_ids:[],artifact_ids:[],approval_ids:[],proof_ids:[]}]}`.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:4835:+- `leads.json`: posting leads found by `scout`, including the bench.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:4837:+- `sources.json`: boards, newsletters, communities, saved searches, and job channels.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:4839:+- `targets.json`: employer/segment target list and Top 10.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:4841:+- `capabilities.json`: setup results and best available execution rungs.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:4843:+- `metrics.json`: quotas, weekly funnel metrics, and the mutable evidence inbox index.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:4844:+  Schema: `{version, updated_at, quotas:{weekly_applications}, weeks:[{week_start,outreach_sent,applications,screens,interviews,offers,response_rate?,notes?}], evidence_inbox:[{id,event_id,source,profile_sections:[],claim,status,created_at,drained_at?}]}`.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:4845:+- `approvals.jsonl`: append-only agent-written approval records, one JSON object per line.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:4847:+- `events.jsonl`: append-only server-written request events, one JSON object per line.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:4858:+Legacy `TARGETS.md` and `PIPELINE.md` may be read during migration, but v2 authority is `targets.json` and `pipeline.json`.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:4862:+Profile-relevant events are tagged into `metrics.json.evidence_inbox`: lead approvals/dismissals, CV rejection reasons, recurring reply reason codes, stage-change patterns, and prototype debriefs. `profile` and `review` drain this inbox into dated `PROFILE.md` updates using the confidence-mark discipline, then mark inbox entries drained.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:4872:+Steve Dalton's LAMP method, adapted. `targets.json` is the operational source of truth for employers, projects, fellowships, agencies, open-source orgs with paid roles, or client segments. See [state.md](state.md) for the schema. `scout` handles posting sources and leads; this command handles who is worth pursuing.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:4892:+Use LAMP fields in `targets.json`:
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:4919:+Updated `targets.json`: full scored list, Top 10, why-them notes, insider candidates, retired targets with reason codes. Register the Top 5 as `pipeline.json` cards and hand off to `outreach` or `scout`.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:4933:+A local career ops skill: interview the person to define what good work means for them, then operate the search from one folder for one person — setup, futures, prototypes, positioning, targets, scouting, outreach, applications, reconciliation, pipeline, approvals, and daily/weekly loops.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:4944:+Operational state is JSON/JSONL; narrative state stays Markdown. The agent is the sole state writer, with the local server limited to appending request events. Outbound work uses the execution ladder and hard gates in `reference/execution.md`.
