goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:9066:+Goodwork v2 turns the skill into a local operator: one project folder equals one person. It runs on the user's machine, keeps sensitive state local, uses connected services when available, and degrades to draft-and-instruct when no connector or browser path exists.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:9068:+The agent is the only writer of state. The server is a local review surface: it renders projections from state and appends user request events.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:9074:+- **Server:** Python stdlib only, about 100 lines in the implementation phase. It binds `127.0.0.1` on a random port, serves regenerated HTML projections, and exposes one POST endpoint that appends request events.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:9075:+- **Remote layer:** Tailscale `serve` proxies the local server onto the user's tailnet. `tailscale funnel` is banned.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:9076:+- **Connectors:** Gmail creates drafts only; Calendar proposes slots or creates approved holds. Browser automation uses the persistent Chrome profile. WhatsApp Web is read-only and opt-in after risk disclosure.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:9081:+Operational state files are JSON/JSONL: `pipeline.json`, `leads.json`, `sources.json`, `targets.json`, `capabilities.json`, `metrics.json`, `approvals.jsonl`, and `events.jsonl`.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:9091:+- Bind `127.0.0.1:0`; record the chosen port in process output, not state.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:9092:+- Generate a 128-bit random session token at startup.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:9093:+- Serve only while pending approvals or review items exist, then idle-timeout after the queue drains.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:9094:+- On crash or restart, recover from `events.jsonl`; the next agent command drains events after the saved cursor.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:9098:+Every request requires the current session token. Accept it in a query parameter for GET pages and in the POST body for `/event`; clients may also send `X-Goodwork-Token`. Never accept cookie-only authentication.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:9100:+The Tailscale host is stable and bookmarkable. The session URL or page form token may change per server run; setup records this as a live-session token, not a long-lived secret. Responses set `Referrer-Policy: no-referrer` so tokenized URLs are not leaked through referrers.
