goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:9195:+- **Localhost CSRF:** any webpage can POST to localhost. `/event` requires the session token in the POST body or header and rejects missing or wrong tokens. Origin checks are advisory only; token validation is the gate.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:9196:+- **Token leakage:** tokenized URLs are per-session, responses use `Referrer-Policy: no-referrer`, and tokens are not written to git-tracked state.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:9197:+- **Tailnet exposure:** Tailscale `serve` is allowed; `funnel` is banned.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:9198:+- **State integrity:** server appends events only. The agent is the only writer of JSON, JSONL approvals, and Markdown.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:9201:+- **WhatsApp risk:** WhatsApp Web is read-only, opt-in, and disclosed as account-ban/Terms-of-Service risk. No automated sending.
