goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:16274:+The UI click never approves directly. It appends an event; the agent validates gates and writes `approvals.jsonl`.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:16282:+Columns come from `pipeline.json` stages. Cards show target/lead, next action, due date, staleness color, warmth, and badges for approval needed, reply waiting, proof missing, or evidence gap.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:16288:+Setup verifies Tailscale, then exposes the local server with `tailscale serve` to the user's MagicDNS tailnet URL. The URL is for tailnet devices only. If the user declines Tailscale, Goodwork records `desk-only` and serves only on the local machine.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:16290:+Never use `tailscale funnel`. Public internet exposure is outside the v2 contract.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:16292:+Local push notifications say work is ready, for example "3 items pending". They do not need to include a link because the MagicDNS host is stable.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:16296:+Execution uses the ladder in `skills/goodwork/reference/execution.md`: MCP connector, ATS-direct, authenticated Chrome, manual fallback. Approval, hash, evidence, quota, truth, and proof gates are hard preconditions.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:16298:+Gmail execution creates drafts only. The user sends from Gmail. Browser and ATS submissions record confirmation screenshots as proof.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:16302:+- **Localhost CSRF:** any webpage can POST to localhost. `/event` requires the session token in the POST body or header and rejects missing or wrong tokens. Origin checks are advisory only; token validation is the gate.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:16303:+- **Token leakage:** tokenized URLs are per-session, responses use `Referrer-Policy: no-referrer`, and tokens are not written to git-tracked state.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:16304:+- **Tailnet exposure:** Tailscale `serve` is allowed; `funnel` is banned.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:16305:+- **State integrity:** server appends events only. The agent is the only writer of JSON, JSONL approvals, and Markdown.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:16308:+- **WhatsApp risk:** WhatsApp Web is read-only, opt-in, and disclosed as account-ban/Terms-of-Service risk. No automated sending.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:16318:+A local career ops skill: interview the person to define what good work means for them, then operate the search from one folder for one person — setup, futures, prototypes, positioning, targets, scouting, outreach, applications, reconciliation, pipeline, approvals, and daily/weekly loops.
