goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:16525:+- **Approval gate.** Before any outbound draft creation, send, submit, publish, or browser final action, `approvals.jsonl` must contain a matching approval record.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:16526:+- **Hash gate.** The approval `content_hash` must match the current artifact. A UI click is only a request; if content changed after render, re-present the artifact and do not approve.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:16528:+- **Quota gate.** Weekly application quota in `metrics.json` is a hard cap. Do not exceed it without an explicit quota change recorded before execution.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:16534:+Per-item approvals cover exactly one artifact. Session-batch approvals are allowed only when `covers` lists every item ID and content hash included in the batch.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:16536:+Record schema lives in [state.md](state.md). Required fields: `id`, `timestamp`, `item_id`, `channel`, `granularity`, `content_hash`, `covers`, and `approved_by`. Include `source_event_id` when approval came from the UI.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:16540:+An execution run is complete only when every requested outbound item has one of these states recorded against its pipeline card: executed with proof, draft created for user send, blocked by a named gate, or manual fallback produced.
