goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:20568:+Goodwork v2 turns the skill into a local operator: one project folder equals one person. It runs on the user's machine, keeps sensitive state local, uses connected services when available, and degrades to draft-and-instruct when no connector or browser path exists.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:20570:+The agent is the only writer of state. The server is a local review surface: it renders projections from state and appends user request events.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:20576:+- **Server:** Python stdlib only, about 100 lines in the implementation phase. It binds `127.0.0.1` on a random port, serves regenerated HTML projections, and exposes one POST endpoint that appends request events.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:20577:+- **Remote layer:** Tailscale `serve` proxies the local server onto the user's tailnet. `tailscale funnel` is banned.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:20578:+- **Connectors:** Gmail creates drafts only; Calendar proposes slots or creates approved holds. Browser automation uses the persistent Chrome profile. WhatsApp Web is read-only and opt-in after risk disclosure.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:20583:+Operational state files are JSON/JSONL: `pipeline.json`, `leads.json`, `sources.json`, `targets.json`, `capabilities.json`, `metrics.json`, `approvals.jsonl`, and `events.jsonl`.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:20593:+- Bind `127.0.0.1:0`; record the chosen port in process output, not state.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:20594:+- Generate a 128-bit random session token at startup.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:20595:+- Serve only while pending approvals or review items exist, then idle-timeout after the queue drains.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:20596:+- On crash or restart, recover from `events.jsonl`; the next agent command drains events after the saved cursor.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:20600:+Every request requires the current session token. Accept it in a query parameter for GET pages and in the POST body for `/event`; clients may also send `X-Goodwork-Token`. Never accept cookie-only authentication.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:20602:+The Tailscale host is stable and bookmarkable. The session URL or page form token may change per server run; setup records this as a live-session token, not a long-lived secret. Responses set `Referrer-Policy: no-referrer` so tokenized URLs are not leaked through referrers.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:20606:+`GET /health?token=...`
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:20609:+`GET /approval?token=...&item_id=...`
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:20610:+: Renders one approval item, with approve, reject-with-reason, edit-then-approve, and optional batch controls.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:20612:+`GET /diff?token=...&artifact_id=...`
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:20615:+`GET /kanban?token=...`
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:20616:+: Renders the pipeline projection from `pipeline.json`.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:20618:+`GET /static/...?...token=...`
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:20619:+: Serves vendored assets only when token is present.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:20622:+: The only POST endpoint. Validates the token, appends one event to `events.jsonl`, and returns an event ID. It never writes approvals or operational state.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:20633:+  "type": "approval_requested",
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:20635:+  "page": "approval",
