goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:20911:+1. **MCP connector.** Use connected services first. Email is Gmail drafts only; the user sends from Gmail, giving a physical send gate. Calendar connectors may propose slots and create drafts/holds only after approval.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:20914:+4. **Manual fallback.** Produce the final draft, field-by-field instructions, and any files. The user performs the action.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:20916:+When no rung is connected, degrade to draft-and-instruct. Do not silently skip an execution attempt; record the chosen rung or the fallback.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:20920:+- **Approval gate.** Before any outbound draft creation, send, submit, publish, or browser final action, `approvals.jsonl` must contain a matching approval record.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:20921:+- **Hash gate.** The approval `content_hash` must match the current artifact. A UI click is only a request; if content changed after render, re-present the artifact and do not approve.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:20923:+- **Quota gate.** Weekly application quota in `metrics.json` is a hard cap. Do not exceed it without an explicit quota change recorded before execution.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:20929:+Per-item approvals cover exactly one artifact. Session-batch approvals are allowed only when `covers` lists every item ID and content hash included in the batch.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:20931:+Record schema lives in [state.md](state.md). Required fields: `id`, `timestamp`, `item_id`, `channel`, `granularity`, `content_hash`, `covers`, and `approved_by`. Include `source_event_id` when approval came from the UI.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:20935:+An execution run is complete only when every requested outbound item has one of these states recorded against its pipeline card: executed with proof, draft created for user send, blocked by a named gate, or manual fallback produced.
