goodwork-workspace/v2/BRIEF-v2-spec.md:14:- `reconcile`: inbound sweep — Gmail, WhatsApp Web (read-only), LinkedIn messages → match replies to pipeline IDs, advance stages, detect interview requests (propose calendar slots via connector), draft replies for approval. `daily` runs reconcile FIRST (inbound changes today's queue). Cadence is whatever setup recorded.
goodwork-workspace/v2/BRIEF-v2-spec.md:16:**Execution ladder** (recorded in `capabilities.json`, consulted by `apply`/`outreach`, best available rung wins): (1) MCP connector (email as Gmail DRAFTS the user sends — a physically enforced gate); (2) ATS-direct via Greenhouse/Lever/Ashby public application endpoints; (3) authenticated Chrome (persistent profile; Playwright or Claude-in-Chrome; `.env` creds only where a profile can't hold a session); (4) manual fallback (draft + instructions).
goodwork-workspace/v2/BRIEF-v2-spec.md:18:**Gates (hard preconditions on execution, not advice).** Every outbound artifact requires an `approvals.jsonl` record: item ID, content hash, timestamp, channel, granularity. Per-item approval AND session-batch both supported (batch lists exactly what it covers). A UI click is a REQUEST — the agent validates the content hash before recording approval; hash mismatch (content edited after render) → re-present, never send. Evidence gate (~70% of must-haves evidenced in profile) and the weekly application quota are hard preconditions. Browser/ATS submissions screenshot the confirmation page as proof. Never invent experience/metrics/credentials, ever.
goodwork-workspace/v2/BRIEF-v2-spec.md:30:Router stays thin; each command's material lives in its own reference file; one meaning, one home (the execution ladder, gate rules, and state model each get exactly one authoritative location, other files point to it); no restating what SKILL.md already says; completion criteria checkable and exhaustive; hunt leading words; keep every reference file lean.
goodwork-workspace/v2/BRIEF-v2-spec.md:37:- New: `reference/state.md` — the single home for the state model: file inventory, JSON schemas (inline, concise), ID conventions, agent-sole-writer rule, evidence inbox.
goodwork-workspace/v2/BRIEF-v2-spec.md:39:- Updated: `framework.md` (workspace section → v2 state model, pointing at state.md), `apply.md`/`outreach.md` (grow execution sections that POINT at execution.md rather than restate it), `pipeline.md` (pipeline.json), `targets.md` (targets.json), `daily.md` (reconcile first), `profile.md` (evidence inbox), `review.md` (drains evidence inbox), `README.md`.
goodwork-workspace/v2/BRIEF-v2-spec.md:44:- `ROADMAP.md` — the six build slices (setup+capabilities+JSON migration → reconcile/Gmail → UI server+pages → ATS-direct apply → browser fallback → WhatsApp read-only), each with its definition-of-done AND the eval gates it adds to `goodwork-workspace/eval/` (e.g. "no submission without approval record", "quota never exceeded", fake local ATS form for browser-path tests).
skills/goodwork/reference/framework.md:60:The state model, file inventory, schemas, ID rules, agent-sole-writer rule, and evidence inbox live in [state.md](state.md). Create files on first use. Update cumulatively; don't regenerate. Treat contents as sensitive personal data: never share or publish them without explicit instruction.
goodwork-workspace/v2/SPEC.md:5:Goodwork v2 turns the skill into a local operator: one project folder equals one person. It runs on the user's machine, keeps sensitive state local, uses connected services when available, and degrades to draft-and-instruct when no connector or browser path exists.
goodwork-workspace/v2/SPEC.md:15:- **Connectors:** Gmail creates drafts only; Calendar proposes slots or creates approved holds. Browser automation uses the persistent Chrome profile. WhatsApp Web is read-only and opt-in after risk disclosure.
goodwork-workspace/v2/SPEC.md:130:Gmail execution creates drafts only. The user sends from Gmail. Browser and ATS submissions record confirmation screenshots as proof.
skills/goodwork/reference/outreach.md:3:Referrals and weak ties carry most opportunity; portals carry volume. This command runs the human layer: the listening tour, informational interviews, referral asks, cold outreach, and follow-up cadence. Execution uses [execution.md](execution.md); do not create drafts, send, or automate browser work without its approval and hash gates.
skills/goodwork/reference/outreach.md:7:Read `capabilities.json` and [execution.md](execution.md) before turning any message into a Gmail draft, LinkedIn message, or manual send package. Gmail is draft-only; the user sends. Log the chosen rung and resulting thread IDs back to `pipeline.json`.
goodwork-workspace/v2/ROADMAP.md:10:- Legacy `TARGETS.md` and `PIPELINE.md` migrate into `targets.json` and `pipeline.json` without losing campaign facts.
goodwork-workspace/v2/ROADMAP.md:22:## 2. Reconcile And Gmail
goodwork-workspace/v2/ROADMAP.md:26:- Gmail connector sweep reads replies, recruiter mail, rejections, interview logistics, and draft/send status.
goodwork-workspace/v2/ROADMAP.md:29:- Interview requests produce calendar-slot proposals and reply drafts, not sends.
goodwork-workspace/v2/ROADMAP.md:34:- `gmail-never-sends`: reconcile can create drafts only after approval and never sends mail.
skills/goodwork/reference/execution.md:3:This is the single source of truth for executing outbound Goodwork actions. Read it before any command creates a Gmail draft, sends, submits, publishes, uses ATS endpoints, or automates authenticated browser work.
skills/goodwork/reference/execution.md:9:1. **MCP connector.** Use connected services first. Email is Gmail drafts only; the user sends from Gmail, giving a physical send gate. Calendar connectors may propose slots and create drafts/holds only after approval.
skills/goodwork/reference/execution.md:12:4. **Manual fallback.** Produce the final draft, field-by-field instructions, and any files. The user performs the action.
skills/goodwork/reference/execution.md:14:When no rung is connected, degrade to draft-and-instruct. Do not silently skip an execution attempt; record the chosen rung or the fallback.
skills/goodwork/reference/execution.md:16:## Hard Gates
skills/goodwork/reference/execution.md:18:- **Approval gate.** Before any outbound draft creation, send, submit, publish, or browser final action, `approvals.jsonl` must contain a matching approval record.
skills/goodwork/reference/execution.md:20:- **Evidence gate.** Applications require evidenced profile support for about 70% of must-have requirements. If the gate fails, stop and propose the cheapest proof artifact or prototype.
skills/goodwork/reference/execution.md:21:- **Quota gate.** Weekly application quota in `metrics.json` is a hard cap. Do not exceed it without an explicit quota change recorded before execution.
skills/goodwork/reference/execution.md:33:An execution run is complete only when every requested outbound item has one of these states recorded against its pipeline card: executed with proof, draft created for user send, blocked by a named gate, or manual fallback produced.
skills/goodwork/reference/craft.md:28:If two rounds of crafting move nothing, run "imagining the quit" as a prototype: draft the resignation conversation, price out the runway, and do a listening tour on the outside option — *before* resigning. If the exit still wins, quit well: reputation and relationships intact, and route to `targets` with the diagnosis as targeting data (you now know precisely what the next role must and must not contain).
skills/goodwork/reference/state.md:1:# state - v2 workspace state model
skills/goodwork/reference/state.md:7:One project folder is one person. The `goodwork/` folder holds state, vendored UI assets, the persistent Chrome profile, and a gitignored `.env`. Never install Goodwork globally. Degrade to draft-and-instruct when a capability is absent.
skills/goodwork/reference/state.md:11:The agent is the sole writer of state files. The server never mutates JSON or Markdown and never appends approvals; it only appends user request events to `events.jsonl`. The agent drains events, validates them, and writes resulting state changes.
skills/goodwork/reference/state.md:44:Legacy `TARGETS.md` and `PIPELINE.md` may be read during migration, but v2 authority is `targets.json` and `pipeline.json`.
skills/goodwork/reference/apply.md:7:Read [execution.md](execution.md) before creating an application package for submission or draft creation. That file owns the execution ladder, approval records, content hashes, evidence gate, weekly quota gate, and proof capture. This command decides whether the application is worth attempting and prepares the truthful package.
skills/goodwork/reference/reconcile.md:11:1. Gmail via connector: replies, recruiter mail, interview logistics, rejection notices, and sent/draft status where available.
skills/goodwork/reference/reconcile.md:31:Updated `pipeline.json`, drafted replies or calendar proposals awaiting approval, unmatched inbound items needing user judgment, and today's changed priorities for `daily`.
skills/goodwork/reference/setup.md:8:2. Connect Gmail and Calendar MCP connectors when available. Record unavailable connectors rather than blocking.
skills/goodwork/reference/setup.md:22:Setup is complete when `capabilities.json` truthfully records every capability, the approval/event loop is tested or explicitly marked unavailable, and the next command knows whether it can execute or must draft-and-instruct.
skills/goodwork/reference/pipeline.md:3:`pipeline.json` is the operational source of truth for live campaign work. UI kanban pages are projections from this file; the server never writes it. See [state.md](state.md) for the schema and ID rules.
skills/goodwork/reference/pipeline.md:17:- Update immediately on any event: reply, ghost, interview, rejection, user drag request, approval, draft, submission, or follow-up.
