goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-review.log:2225:goodwork-workspace/v2/BRIEF-v2-spec.md:16:**Execution ladder** (recorded in `capabilities.json`, consulted by `apply`/`outreach`, best available rung wins): (1) MCP connector (email as Gmail DRAFTS the user sends — a physically enforced gate); (2) ATS-direct via Greenhouse/Lever/Ashby public application endpoints; (3) authenticated Chrome (persistent profile; Playwright or Claude-in-Chrome; `.env` creds only where a profile can't hold a session); (4) manual fallback (draft + instructions).
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-review.log:2226:goodwork-workspace/v2/BRIEF-v2-spec.md:18:**Gates (hard preconditions on execution, not advice).** Every outbound artifact requires an `approvals.jsonl` record: item ID, content hash, timestamp, channel, granularity. Per-item approval AND session-batch both supported (batch lists exactly what it covers). A UI click is a REQUEST — the agent validates the content hash before recording approval; hash mismatch (content edited after render) → re-present, never send. Evidence gate (~70% of must-haves evidenced in profile) and the weekly application quota are hard preconditions. Browser/ATS submissions screenshot the confirmation page as proof. Never invent experience/metrics/credentials, ever.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-review.log:2230:goodwork-workspace/v2/BRIEF-v2-spec.md:37:- New: `reference/state.md` — the single home for the state model: file inventory, JSON schemas (inline, concise), ID conventions, agent-sole-writer rule, evidence inbox.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-review.log:2232:goodwork-workspace/v2/BRIEF-v2-spec.md:39:- Updated: `framework.md` (workspace section → v2 state model, pointing at state.md), `apply.md`/`outreach.md` (grow execution sections that POINT at execution.md rather than restate it), `pipeline.md` (pipeline.json), `targets.md` (targets.json), `daily.md` (reconcile first), `profile.md` (evidence inbox), `review.md` (drains evidence inbox), `README.md`.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-review.log:2234:goodwork-workspace/v2/BRIEF-v2-spec.md:44:- `ROADMAP.md` — the six build slices (setup+capabilities+JSON migration → reconcile/Gmail → UI server+pages → ATS-direct apply → browser fallback → WhatsApp read-only), each with its definition-of-done AND the eval gates it adds to `goodwork-workspace/eval/` (e.g. "no submission without approval record", "quota never exceeded", fake local ATS form for browser-path tests).
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-review.log:2236:skills/goodwork/reference/framework.md:60:The state model, file inventory, schemas, ID rules, agent-sole-writer rule, and evidence inbox live in [state.md](state.md). Create files on first use. Update cumulatively; don't regenerate. Treat contents as sensitive personal data: never share or publish them without explicit instruction.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-review.log:2237:goodwork-workspace/v2/SPEC.md:5:Goodwork v2 turns the skill into a local operator: one project folder equals one person. It runs on the user's machine, keeps sensitive state local, uses connected services when available, and degrades to draft-and-instruct when no connector or browser path exists.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-review.log:2241:goodwork-workspace/v2/SPEC.md:15:- **Connectors:** Gmail creates drafts only; Calendar proposes slots or creates approved holds. Browser automation uses the persistent Chrome profile. WhatsApp Web is read-only and opt-in after risk disclosure.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-review.log:2272:goodwork-workspace/v2/SPEC.md:130:Gmail execution creates drafts only. The user sends from Gmail. Browser and ATS submissions record confirmation screenshots as proof.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-review.log:2287:goodwork-workspace/v2/BRIEF-v2-review.md:1:# Task: Adversarial review of the Goodwork v2 spec + skill draft, fix in place
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-review.log:2288:goodwork-workspace/v2/BRIEF-v2-review.md:3:Review everything the v2 drafting pass produced: `goodwork-workspace/v2/SPEC.md`, `SCHEMAS.md`, `ROADMAP.md`, and all changed/new files under `skills/goodwork/`. The authoritative requirements: `goodwork-workspace/v2/BRIEF-v2-spec.md`. The skill-authoring rules: `.claude/skills/writing-great-skills/SKILL.md` + `GLOSSARY.md`. Fix directly; log every fix as one line in `goodwork-workspace/v2/REVIEW-FINDINGS.md` (severity: blocker/major/minor); put anything needing a human decision under "Open questions" instead of guessing.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-review.log:2289:goodwork-workspace/v2/BRIEF-v2-review.md:5:## Adjudicated calls (the drafter self-reported five risky calls — these verdicts are final, implement them)
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-review.log:2293:goodwork-workspace/v2/BRIEF-v2-review.md:11:5. Approval required BEFORE Gmail draft creation — REJECTED. Creating a draft in the user's own Gmail is not outbound; the draft IS the review surface and the user pressing send in Gmail IS the physically enforced gate (that was the brief's design). Fix execution.md/SPEC: no approval record needed to create a draft; define what, if anything, gets logged for email (e.g. a draft-created event for reconcile matching). Connector-sent email (if ever) still requires full approval.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-review.log:2294:goodwork-workspace/v2/BRIEF-v2-review.md:15:1. **Brief conformance**: walk BRIEF-v2-spec.md's locked decisions one by one against the draft — flag anything missing, weakened, or invented beyond the brief's room.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-review.log:2295:goodwork-workspace/v2/BRIEF-v2-review.md:16:2. **Single source of truth**: state model must live only in state.md, ladder/gates only in execution.md; other files may point, never restate. Hunt duplication across all 19 skill files.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-review.log:2298:goodwork-workspace/v2/BRIEF-v2-review.md:20:6. **Gate integrity walkthrough**: trace one application end-to-end through the draft docs (tailor → render review → click approve → hash validate → execute → screenshot proof → pipeline update). Any step where the docs are ambiguous or contradictory is a finding. Do the same for a batch approval and for a hash-mismatch rejection.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-review.log:2301:skills/goodwork/reference/execution.md:3:This is the single source of truth for executing outbound Goodwork actions. Read it before any command creates a Gmail draft, sends, submits, publishes, uses ATS endpoints, or automates authenticated browser work.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-review.log:2303:skills/goodwork/reference/execution.md:9:1. **MCP connector.** Use connected services first. Email is Gmail drafts only; the user sends from Gmail, giving a physical send gate. Calendar connectors may propose slots and create drafts/holds only after approval.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-review.log:2304:skills/goodwork/reference/execution.md:12:4. **Manual fallback.** Produce the final draft, field-by-field instructions, and any files. The user performs the action.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-review.log:2305:skills/goodwork/reference/execution.md:14:When no rung is connected, degrade to draft-and-instruct. Do not silently skip an execution attempt; record the chosen rung or the fallback.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-review.log:2306:skills/goodwork/reference/execution.md:18:- **Approval gate.** Before any outbound draft creation, send, submit, publish, or browser final action, `approvals.jsonl` must contain a matching approval record.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-review.log:2308:skills/goodwork/reference/execution.md:21:- **Quota gate.** Weekly application quota in `metrics.json` is a hard cap. Do not exceed it without an explicit quota change recorded before execution.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-review.log:2311:skills/goodwork/reference/execution.md:33:An execution run is complete only when every requested outbound item has one of these states recorded against its pipeline card: executed with proof, draft created for user send, blocked by a named gate, or manual fallback produced.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-review.log:2312:skills/goodwork/reference/outreach.md:3:Referrals and weak ties carry most opportunity; portals carry volume. This command runs the human layer: the listening tour, informational interviews, referral asks, cold outreach, and follow-up cadence. Execution uses [execution.md](execution.md); do not create drafts, send, or automate browser work without its approval and hash gates.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-review.log:2313:skills/goodwork/reference/outreach.md:7:Read `capabilities.json` and [execution.md](execution.md) before turning any message into a Gmail draft, LinkedIn message, or manual send package. Gmail is draft-only; the user sends. Log the chosen rung and resulting thread IDs back to `pipeline.json`.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-review.log:2327:skills/goodwork/reference/setup.md:22:Setup is complete when `capabilities.json` truthfully records every capability, the approval/event loop is tested or explicitly marked unavailable, and the next command knows whether it can execute or must draft-and-instruct.
