goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-review.log:3213:goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:4439:+Read [execution.md](execution.md) before creating an application package for submission or draft creation. That file owns the execution ladder, approval records, content hashes, evidence gate, weekly quota gate, and proof capture. This command decides whether the application is worth attempting and prepares the truthful package.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-review.log:3226:goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:4504:+This is the single source of truth for executing outbound Goodwork actions. Read it before any command creates a Gmail draft, sends, submits, publishes, uses ATS endpoints, or automates authenticated browser work.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-review.log:3228:goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:4510:+1. **MCP connector.** Use connected services first. Email is Gmail drafts only; the user sends from Gmail, giving a physical send gate. Calendar connectors may propose slots and create drafts/holds only after approval.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-review.log:3229:goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:4513:+4. **Manual fallback.** Produce the final draft, field-by-field instructions, and any files. The user performs the action.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-review.log:3230:goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:4515:+When no rung is connected, degrade to draft-and-instruct. Do not silently skip an execution attempt; record the chosen rung or the fallback.
