goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-review.log:4773:goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:14837:+- **Connectors:** Gmail creates drafts only; Calendar proposes slots or creates approved holds. Browser automation uses the persistent Chrome profile. WhatsApp Web is read-only and opt-in after risk disclosure.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-review.log:4804:goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:14952:+Gmail execution creates drafts only. The user sends from Gmail. Browser and ATS submissions record confirmation screenshots as proof.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-review.log:4811:goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:14983:+Operational state is JSON/JSONL; narrative state stays Markdown. The agent is the sole state writer, with the local server limited to appending request events. Outbound work uses the execution ladder and hard gates in `reference/execution.md`.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-review.log:4813:goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:15015:+- The agent is the sole writer of workspace state files. The local server may append only request events; the agent validates and applies them.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-review.log:4814:goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:15016:+- Gate before send or submit: use [reference/execution.md](reference/execution.md) for approvals, content hashes, evidence, quotas, execution ladder, and proof capture.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-review.log:4816:goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:15043:+| `reconcile` | Sustain | Sweep inbound messages, match replies, update stages, and draft responses | [reference/reconcile.md](reference/reconcile.md) |
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-review.log:4817:goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:15059:+6. **State touch**: when a command reads or writes operational JSON/JSONL, load [reference/state.md](reference/state.md). When it creates, sends, submits, drafts, or automates, load [reference/execution.md](reference/execution.md).
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-review.log:4818:goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:15079:-- Outreach and application drafts: polished final text first, then rationale. Always show before any send.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-review.log:4819:goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:15083:+- Outreach and application drafts: polished final text first, then rationale. Execution waits for the gates in [reference/execution.md](reference/execution.md).
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-review.log:4820:goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:15099:+Read [execution.md](execution.md) before creating an application package for submission or draft creation. That file owns the execution ladder, approval records, content hashes, evidence gate, weekly quota gate, and proof capture. This command decides whether the application is worth attempting and prepares the truthful package.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-review.log:4833:goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:15164:+This is the single source of truth for executing outbound Goodwork actions. Read it before any command creates a Gmail draft, sends, submits, publishes, uses ATS endpoints, or automates authenticated browser work.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-review.log:4835:goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:15170:+1. **MCP connector.** Use connected services first. Email is Gmail drafts only; the user sends from Gmail, giving a physical send gate. Calendar connectors may propose slots and create drafts/holds only after approval.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-review.log:4836:goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:15173:+4. **Manual fallback.** Produce the final draft, field-by-field instructions, and any files. The user performs the action.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-review.log:4837:goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:15175:+When no rung is connected, degrade to draft-and-instruct. Do not silently skip an execution attempt; record the chosen rung or the fallback.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-review.log:4838:goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:15179:+- **Approval gate.** Before any outbound draft creation, send, submit, publish, or browser final action, `approvals.jsonl` must contain a matching approval record.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-review.log:4840:goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:15182:+- **Quota gate.** Weekly application quota in `metrics.json` is a hard cap. Do not exceed it without an explicit quota change recorded before execution.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-review.log:4843:goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:15194:+An execution run is complete only when every requested outbound item has one of these states recorded against its pipeline card: executed with proof, draft created for user send, blocked by a named gate, or manual fallback produced.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-review.log:4845:goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:15209:+The state model, file inventory, schemas, ID rules, agent-sole-writer rule, and evidence inbox live in [state.md](state.md). Create files on first use. Update cumulatively; don't regenerate. Treat contents as sensitive personal data: never share or publish them without explicit instruction.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-review.log:4846:goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:15220:+Referrals and weak ties carry most opportunity; portals carry volume. This command runs the human layer: the listening tour, informational interviews, referral asks, cold outreach, and follow-up cadence. Execution uses [execution.md](execution.md); do not create drafts, send, or automate browser work without its approval and hash gates.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-review.log:4848:goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:15225:+Read `capabilities.json` and [execution.md](execution.md) before turning any message into a Gmail draft, LinkedIn message, or manual send package. Gmail is draft-only; the user sends. Log the chosen rung and resulting thread IDs back to `pipeline.json`.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-review.log:4851:goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:15242:-Drafts for approval, per-conversation prep sheets (their background, why-them, the 10 questions), call debriefs appended to `goodwork/PIPELINE.md`, and niche-hypothesis updates flagged for `NICHE.md`.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-review.log:4853:goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:15253:+`pipeline.json` is the operational source of truth for live campaign work. UI kanban pages are projections from this file; the server never writes it. See [state.md](state.md) for the schema and ID rules.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-review.log:4855:goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:15276:+- Update immediately on any event: reply, ghost, interview, rejection, user drag request, approval, draft, submission, or follow-up.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-review.log:4863:goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:15353:+1. Gmail via connector: replies, recruiter mail, interview logistics, rejection notices, and sent/draft status where available.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-review.log:4867:goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:15373:+Updated `pipeline.json`, drafted replies or calendar proposals awaiting approval, unmatched inbound items needing user judgment, and today's changed priorities for `daily`.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-review.log:4882:goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:15468:+Setup is complete when `capabilities.json` truthfully records every capability, the approval/event loop is tested or explicitly marked unavailable, and the next command knows whether it can execute or must draft-and-instruct.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-review.log:4886:goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:15481:+One project folder is one person. The `goodwork/` folder holds state, vendored UI assets, the persistent Chrome profile, and a gitignored `.env`. Never install Goodwork globally. Degrade to draft-and-instruct when a capability is absent.
