goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:2234:+The agent is the sole writer of state files. The server never mutates JSON or Markdown and never appends approvals; it only appends user request events to `events.jsonl`. The agent drains events, validates them, and writes resulting state changes.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:2267:+Legacy `TARGETS.md` and `PIPELINE.md` may be read during migration, but v2 authority is `targets.json` and `pipeline.json`.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:2303:- Log in `PIPELINE.md`: date, version sent, referral status, follow-up date (insider nudge ~1 week; portal-only, expect silence and let the pipeline carry it).
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:2336:- Log every touch in `PIPELINE.md` with a next-action date; `daily` surfaces what's due.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:2344:Drafts for approval, per-conversation prep sheets (their background, why-them, the 10 questions), call debriefs appended to `goodwork/PIPELINE.md`, and niche-hypothesis updates flagged for `NICHE.md`.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:2349:skills/goodwork/reference/daily.md:9:1. **Due follow-ups** from `PIPELINE.md` (the 3-day/7-day cadence and promised thank-yous) — these are commitments, they go first.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:2355:skills/goodwork/reference/targets.md:33:Write `goodwork/TARGETS.md`: the full scored table, the Top 10 with why-them notes and insider candidates, retired targets with reason codes. Register the Top 5 in `PIPELINE.md` and hand off to `outreach`.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:2357:skills/goodwork/reference/apply.md:24:- Log in `PIPELINE.md`: date, version sent, referral status, follow-up date (insider nudge ~1 week; portal-only, expect silence and let the pipeline carry it).
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:2361:skills/goodwork/reference/outreach.md:26:- Log every touch in `PIPELINE.md` with a next-action date; `daily` surfaces what's due.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:2363:skills/goodwork/reference/outreach.md:34:Drafts for approval, per-conversation prep sheets (their background, why-them, the 10 questions), call debriefs appended to `goodwork/PIPELINE.md`, and niche-hypothesis updates flagged for `NICHE.md`.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:2365:skills/goodwork/reference/review.md:3:Thirty minutes, once a week, same day each week. The review closes the loop between the campaign (what happened) and the profile (what it means). It reads everything: `PIPELINE.md`, `JOURNAL.md`, `EXPERIMENTS.md`, `TARGETS.md`, `NICHE.md`, `PROFILE.md`.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:2369:skills/goodwork/reference/pipeline.md:3:One file, `goodwork/PIPELINE.md`, is the single source of truth for the campaign. `daily` reads it every morning; `review` reads it every week. Keep it current or the whole ops layer rots.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:2372:skills/goodwork/reference/pipeline.md:34:An updated `PIPELINE.md`, today's due actions pushed to `daily`, and any diagnosis with its routing (which command fixes the constriction).
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:2376:skills/goodwork/reference/framework.md:55:All state lives in a `goodwork/` directory in the working directory (or where the user says): `PROFILE.md`, `ODYSSEYS.md`, `EXPERIMENTS.md`, `NICHE.md`, `TARGETS.md`, `PIPELINE.md`, `JOURNAL.md`. Create files on first use. Update, don't regenerate — these accumulate evidence over weeks. Treat their contents as sensitive personal data: never share or publish them without explicit instruction.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:2409:+- The agent is the sole writer of workspace state files. The local server may append only request events; the agent validates and applies them.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:2410:+- Gate before send or submit: use [reference/execution.md](reference/execution.md) for approvals, content hashes, evidence, quotas, execution ladder, and proof capture.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:2437:+| `reconcile` | Sustain | Sweep inbound messages, match replies, update stages, and draft responses | [reference/reconcile.md](reference/reconcile.md) |
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:2453:+6. **State touch**: when a command reads or writes operational JSON/JSONL, load [reference/state.md](reference/state.md). When it creates, sends, submits, drafts, or automates, load [reference/execution.md](reference/execution.md).
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:2473:-- Outreach and application drafts: polished final text first, then rationale. Always show before any send.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:2477:+- Outreach and application drafts: polished final text first, then rationale. Execution waits for the gates in [reference/execution.md](reference/execution.md).
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:2489:+This is the single source of truth for executing outbound Goodwork actions. Read it before any command creates a Gmail draft, sends, submits, publishes, uses ATS endpoints, or automates authenticated browser work.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:2495:+1. **MCP connector.** Use connected services first. Email is Gmail drafts only; the user sends from Gmail, giving a physical send gate. Calendar connectors may propose slots and create drafts/holds only after approval.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:2498:+4. **Manual fallback.** Produce the final draft, field-by-field instructions, and any files. The user performs the action.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:2500:+When no rung is connected, degrade to draft-and-instruct. Do not silently skip an execution attempt; record the chosen rung or the fallback.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:2502:+## Hard Gates
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:2504:+- **Approval gate.** Before any outbound draft creation, send, submit, publish, or browser final action, `approvals.jsonl` must contain a matching approval record.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:2506:+- **Evidence gate.** Applications require evidenced profile support for about 70% of must-have requirements. If the gate fails, stop and propose the cheapest proof artifact or prototype.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:2507:+- **Quota gate.** Weekly application quota in `metrics.json` is a hard cap. Do not exceed it without an explicit quota change recorded before execution.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:2519:+An execution run is complete only when every requested outbound item has one of these states recorded against its pipeline card: executed with proof, draft created for user send, blocked by a named gate, or manual fallback produced.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:2536:+1. Gmail via connector: replies, recruiter mail, interview logistics, rejection notices, and sent/draft status where available.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:2556:+Updated `pipeline.json`, drafted replies or calendar proposals awaiting approval, unmatched inbound items needing user judgment, and today's changed priorities for `daily`.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:2610:+2. Connect Gmail and Calendar MCP connectors when available. Record unavailable connectors rather than blocking.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:2624:+Setup is complete when `capabilities.json` truthfully records every capability, the approval/event loop is tested or explicitly marked unavailable, and the next command knows whether it can execute or must draft-and-instruct.
