goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:11051:+The agent is the sole writer of state files. The server never mutates JSON or Markdown and never appends approvals; it only appends user request events to `events.jsonl`. The agent drains events, validates them, and writes resulting state changes.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:11084:+Legacy `TARGETS.md` and `PIPELINE.md` may be read during migration, but v2 authority is `targets.json` and `pipeline.json`.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:11144:-Write `goodwork/TARGETS.md`: the full scored table, the Top 10 with why-them notes and insider candidates, retired targets with reason codes. Register the Top 5 in `PIPELINE.md` and hand off to `outreach`.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:11189:+- Legacy `TARGETS.md` and `PIPELINE.md` migrate into `targets.json` and `pipeline.json` without losing campaign facts.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:11201:+## 2. Reconcile And Gmail
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:11205:+- Gmail connector sweep reads replies, recruiter mail, rejections, interview logistics, and draft/send status.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:11208:+- Interview requests produce calendar-slot proposals and reply drafts, not sends.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:11213:+- `gmail-never-sends`: reconcile can create drafts only after approval and never sends mail.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:11295:+Schemas here mirror the skill state model and add example records for implementation planning. All timestamps are ISO 8601 with timezone. IDs are stable and never reused.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:11733:+Goodwork v2 turns the skill into a local operator: one project folder equals one person. It runs on the user's machine, keeps sensitive state local, uses connected services when available, and degrades to draft-and-instruct when no connector or browser path exists.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:11743:+- **Connectors:** Gmail creates drafts only; Calendar proposes slots or creates approved holds. Browser automation uses the persistent Chrome profile. WhatsApp Web is read-only and opt-in after risk disclosure.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:11858:+Gmail execution creates drafts only. The user sends from Gmail. Browser and ATS submissions record confirmation screenshots as proof.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:11889:+Operational state is JSON/JSONL; narrative state stays Markdown. The agent is the sole state writer, with the local server limited to appending request events. Outbound work uses the execution ladder and hard gates in `reference/execution.md`.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:11921:+- The agent is the sole writer of workspace state files. The local server may append only request events; the agent validates and applies them.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:11922:+- Gate before send or submit: use [reference/execution.md](reference/execution.md) for approvals, content hashes, evidence, quotas, execution ladder, and proof capture.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:11949:+| `reconcile` | Sustain | Sweep inbound messages, match replies, update stages, and draft responses | [reference/reconcile.md](reference/reconcile.md) |
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:11965:+6. **State touch**: when a command reads or writes operational JSON/JSONL, load [reference/state.md](reference/state.md). When it creates, sends, submits, drafts, or automates, load [reference/execution.md](reference/execution.md).
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:11985:-- Outreach and application drafts: polished final text first, then rationale. Always show before any send.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:11989:+- Outreach and application drafts: polished final text first, then rationale. Execution waits for the gates in [reference/execution.md](reference/execution.md).
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:12005:+Read [execution.md](execution.md) before creating an application package for submission or draft creation. That file owns the execution ladder, approval records, content hashes, evidence gate, weekly quota gate, and proof capture. This command decides whether the application is worth attempting and prepares the truthful package.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:12020:-- Log in `PIPELINE.md`: date, version sent, referral status, follow-up date (insider nudge ~1 week; portal-only, expect silence and let the pipeline carry it).
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:12047:-1. **Due follow-ups** from `PIPELINE.md` (the 3-day/7-day cadence and promised thank-yous) — these are commitments, they go first.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:12070:+This is the single source of truth for executing outbound Goodwork actions. Read it before any command creates a Gmail draft, sends, submits, publishes, uses ATS endpoints, or automates authenticated browser work.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:12076:+1. **MCP connector.** Use connected services first. Email is Gmail drafts only; the user sends from Gmail, giving a physical send gate. Calendar connectors may propose slots and create drafts/holds only after approval.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:12079:+4. **Manual fallback.** Produce the final draft, field-by-field instructions, and any files. The user performs the action.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:12081:+When no rung is connected, degrade to draft-and-instruct. Do not silently skip an execution attempt; record the chosen rung or the fallback.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:12083:+## Hard Gates
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:12085:+- **Approval gate.** Before any outbound draft creation, send, submit, publish, or browser final action, `approvals.jsonl` must contain a matching approval record.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:12087:+- **Evidence gate.** Applications require evidenced profile support for about 70% of must-have requirements. If the gate fails, stop and propose the cheapest proof artifact or prototype.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:12088:+- **Quota gate.** Weekly application quota in `metrics.json` is a hard cap. Do not exceed it without an explicit quota change recorded before execution.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:12100:+An execution run is complete only when every requested outbound item has one of these states recorded against its pipeline card: executed with proof, draft created for user send, blocked by a named gate, or manual fallback produced.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:12109:-All state lives in a `goodwork/` directory in the working directory (or where the user says): `PROFILE.md`, `ODYSSEYS.md`, `EXPERIMENTS.md`, `NICHE.md`, `TARGETS.md`, `PIPELINE.md`, `JOURNAL.md`. Create files on first use. Update, don't regenerate — these accumulate evidence over weeks. Treat their contents as sensitive personal data: never share or publish them without explicit instruction.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:12115:+The state model, file inventory, schemas, ID rules, agent-sole-writer rule, and evidence inbox live in [state.md](state.md). Create files on first use. Update cumulatively; don't regenerate. Treat contents as sensitive personal data: never share or publish them without explicit instruction.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:12126:+Referrals and weak ties carry most opportunity; portals carry volume. This command runs the human layer: the listening tour, informational interviews, referral asks, cold outreach, and follow-up cadence. Execution uses [execution.md](execution.md); do not create drafts, send, or automate browser work without its approval and hash gates.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:12131:+Read `capabilities.json` and [execution.md](execution.md) before turning any message into a Gmail draft, LinkedIn message, or manual send package. Gmail is draft-only; the user sends. Log the chosen rung and resulting thread IDs back to `pipeline.json`.
