goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:14837:+- **Connectors:** Gmail creates drafts only; Calendar proposes slots or creates approved holds. Browser automation uses the persistent Chrome profile. WhatsApp Web is read-only and opt-in after risk disclosure.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:14952:+Gmail execution creates drafts only. The user sends from Gmail. Browser and ATS submissions record confirmation screenshots as proof.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:14983:+Operational state is JSON/JSONL; narrative state stays Markdown. The agent is the sole state writer, with the local server limited to appending request events. Outbound work uses the execution ladder and hard gates in `reference/execution.md`.
goodwork-workspace/v2/codex-spec.log:15015:+- The agent is the sole writer of workspace state files. The local server may append only request events; the agent validates and applies them.
