goodwork-workspace/v2/SPEC.md:99:`await --ids ... --timeout N` is a blocking CLI bridge used by the agent. It tails `events.jsonl` from `goodwork/.await-cursor`, waits for matching item IDs or event IDs, and exits when all requested events arrive, a rejection arrives, or timeout expires.
goodwork-workspace/v2/SPEC.md:106:- `2`: malformed event log or cursor.
goodwork-workspace/v2/SPEC.md:108:Events clicked while no agent is listening are still appended. The next command drains events after the cursor before starting new work; malformed events do not advance the cursor.
goodwork-workspace/v2/SPEC.md:114:Mobile-first and one item per screen. Show the artifact, channel, destination, current content hash, and the exact action requested. Controls: approve, reject-with-reason, edit-then-approve, and batch checkboxes when a session-batch is being requested. Batch events include the exact `covers` list submitted for validation.
goodwork-workspace/v2/SPEC.md:130:Setup verifies Tailscale, then exposes the local server with `tailscale serve` to the user's MagicDNS tailnet URL. The URL is for tailnet devices only. If the user declines Tailscale, Goodwork records `desk-only` and serves only on the local machine.
goodwork-workspace/v2/SPEC.md:132:Never use `tailscale funnel`. Public internet exposure is outside the v2 contract.
goodwork-workspace/v2/SPEC.md:134:Local push notifications say work is ready, for example "3 items pending". They do not need to include a link because the MagicDNS host is stable.
goodwork-workspace/v2/SPEC.md:145:- **Batch approval:** render the batch with every item and hash, append a `session_batch` event with the exact `covers` list, validate every current hash before writing one batch approval record, then execute only the covered items.
goodwork-workspace/v2/SPEC.md:146:- **Hash mismatch:** if any current artifact hash differs from the event or approval `covers`, write no approval and perform no send/submit; re-render the changed item for review.
goodwork-workspace/v2/SPEC.md:150:- **Localhost CSRF:** any webpage can POST to localhost. `/event` requires the session token in the POST body or header and rejects missing or wrong tokens. Origin checks are advisory only; token validation is the gate.
goodwork-workspace/v2/SPEC.md:151:- **Token leakage:** tokenized URLs are per-session, responses use `Referrer-Policy: no-referrer`, and tokens are not written to git-tracked state.
goodwork-workspace/v2/SPEC.md:152:- **Bookmark bootstrap:** the stable host root can mint a fresh token only for a top-level navigation, serves no private state before redirect, uses no cookies, and does not enable CORS.
goodwork-workspace/v2/SPEC.md:153:- **Tailnet exposure:** Tailscale `serve` is allowed; `funnel` is banned.
